      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Given the urgency of the climate crisis, nuclear power is indeed one of the few mature, dispatchable, and low-carbon options that can scale up quickly enough to meet aggressive net-zero targets. Advocates argue that the catastrophic, irreversible damage from climate change far outweighs the manageable, regulated risks of nuclear technology. While no energy source is perfect, nuclear's capacity to provide massive, consistent power without massive emissions makes it a critical component of a rapid transition strategy.",
      "source": "target",
