      "content": "It is an oversimplification to label all opposition as simply ignoring the math; many critics are focused on the flawed implementation and economic realities of nuclear power. While experts acknowledge its role, the debate centers on whether nuclear is *the* silver bullet, or if it's just one tool among many that needs to be paired with massive renewable buildouts. The opposition often raises valid points about regulatory delays, waste management uncertainty, and the immense upfront capital required, which are real-world limiting factors.",
